Japanese Bought Net 505.1 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-05-25T23:57:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/japanese-bought-net-505-1-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended May 20 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 505.1 billion yen ($6.2 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 1.9 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 14.6 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 517.8 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 906.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 5.1 billion yen in stocks, and bought 690 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 1601.9
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  